1. Definitions

1.1. "Contributor"
     means each individual or legal entity that creates, contributes to
     or covers Contributor Modifications with Contributor Material.

1.2. "Contributor Modification"
     means any modification of the Source Code or any derivative
     works that a Contributor creates or contributes to.

1.3. "Covered Software"
     means the Software and any additions to or derivative works of
     the Software that are made available under this License.

1.4. "External Media"
     means any media, hardware, or software that includes Covered
     Software but was not originally released by the copyright holder.

1.5. "Granular Source Code Form"
     means a form of the Source Code for the Covered Software that is
     designed to facilitate independent modification of parts of the
     Covered Software.

1.6. "Large Data File"
     means any file or collection of data that exceeds 20 MegaBytes in
     size.

1.7. "Object Code"
     means any form of the Covered Software that has been converted
     from Source Code, or any binary data not directly readable as
     text.

1.8. "Source Code"
     means the human-readable form of the Covered Software that is
     most convenient for a developer to make changes to.

1.9. "Software"
     means the computer software works, data, and documentation
     that are covered by this License.

1.10. "You" (or "Your")
     means an individual or a legal entity exercising rights under
     this License.

